1
00:00:01,100 --> 00:00:05,790
Himukai's lucky he found out before marriage.

2
00:00:05,790 --> 00:00:09,550
- Yeah, he dodged a bullet.
- I mean, he's the CEO's son.

3
00:00:09,550 --> 00:00:13,600
He can't be marrying a girl
who can't provide him an heir.

4
00:00:28,990 --> 00:00:30,450
<i>Hey!</i>

5
00:00:30,450 --> 00:00:33,950
How's the dreaded farewell party going?

6
00:00:34,980 --> 00:00:36,740
Sui?

7
00:00:36,740 --> 00:00:39,340
Hello?

8
00:00:39,340 --> 00:00:43,850
<i>It's definitely dreadful.
I think I had too much to drink.</i>

9
00:00:44,950 --> 00:00:47,460
Jeez...

10
00:00:47,460 --> 00:00:49,590
Don't get dragged to an afterparty, okay?

11
00:00:49,590 --> 00:00:52,420
Go straight home after this one.

12
00:00:52,420 --> 00:00:55,640
<i>I will. Thanks.</i>

13
00:01:03,810 --> 00:01:06,660
Maybe I'll deploy him, just in case.

14
00:01:06,660 --> 00:01:10,900
Can I ask you something
I've been wondering about?

15
00:01:10,900 --> 00:01:12,470
Sure.

16
00:01:13,370 --> 00:01:16,080
That night...

17
00:01:16,080 --> 00:01:17,810
Which night?

18
00:01:17,810 --> 00:01:19,340
You know.

19
00:01:22,470 --> 00:01:26,300
The night you helped me.

20
00:01:26,300 --> 00:01:28,100
<i>Are you all right?</i>

21
00:01:28,100 --> 00:01:30,850
<i>Yes, thank you.</i>

22
00:01:30,850 --> 00:01:33,250
<i>You're drunk stupid.</i>

23
00:01:44,730 --> 00:01:49,810
Was it a coincidence you were there?

24
00:01:50,910 --> 00:01:52,710
I wonder.

25
00:01:53,940 --> 00:01:57,110
Erika didn't ask you to check on me, did she?

26
00:02:01,610 --> 00:02:04,210
She technically told me not to tell you.

27
00:02:07,280 --> 00:02:10,050
It's a coincidence a dude hit on you, though.

28
00:02:10,050 --> 00:02:14,310
Honestly, I was surprised to see you
actually in trouble.

29
00:02:14,310 --> 00:02:16,440
Sorry.

30
00:02:16,440 --> 00:02:21,570
But thanks to him,
we shared a nice night together.

31
00:02:21,570 --> 00:02:23,390
Hey!

32
00:02:32,460 --> 00:02:34,350
Mao.

33
00:02:37,560 --> 00:02:39,780
Thanks for always helping out.

34
00:02:41,830 --> 00:02:43,610
It's no big deal.

35
00:03:51,580 --> 00:03:54,260
[Idea Construction Office]

36
00:03:59,830 --> 00:04:04,560
Monou, will you join us for our appointment
with the Hayashi's at 11 today?

37
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:06,020
Sure thing.

38
00:04:06,020 --> 00:04:07,870
Then I'll see you there.

39
00:04:26,780 --> 00:04:29,020
Is this what you're looking for?

40
00:04:29,900 --> 00:04:31,490
Yeah.

41
00:04:32,360 --> 00:04:36,160
The Hayashi's are coming
to ask about kitchen renovations.

42
00:04:36,160 --> 00:04:38,990
I've marked some designs I'd recommend.

43
00:04:41,460 --> 00:04:43,190
Thanks.

44
00:04:46,260 --> 00:04:49,660
Hurry, they're arriving soon.

45
00:04:49,660 --> 00:04:51,500
Right. See you around.

46
00:05:27,120 --> 00:05:31,670
I felt like someone was following me home
yesterday night.

47
00:05:31,670 --> 00:05:33,980
What? Following you?

48
00:05:33,980 --> 00:05:37,370
I technically didn't see anyone though...

49
00:05:37,370 --> 00:05:39,390
Is everything all right?

50
00:05:40,130 --> 00:05:44,480
Nana says someone might've been
following her home last night.

51
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:46,620
Following you?

52
00:05:46,620 --> 00:05:48,720
Any ideas on who it could've been?

53
00:05:50,320 --> 00:05:56,440
I thought maybe it was the woman
who visited you, Monou.

54
00:05:56,440 --> 00:05:58,390
Takizawa?

55
00:05:58,390 --> 00:06:01,160
I'm only speculating, of course.

56
00:06:01,750 --> 00:06:03,520
Still...

57
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:09,560
<i>Anyone who stands in my way will see hell.</i>

58
00:06:09,560 --> 00:06:11,950
- What the...
- I'm so sorry!

59
00:06:11,950 --> 00:06:13,100
It's not your fault.

60
00:06:13,100 --> 00:06:16,560
No, it absolutely is.

61
00:06:16,560 --> 00:06:20,280
I can't believe I've implicated you into this.

62
00:06:20,280 --> 00:06:22,040
I am so sorry.

63
00:06:22,040 --> 00:06:24,130
Don't apologize, please.

64
00:06:24,130 --> 00:06:25,920
Sui.

65
00:06:33,150 --> 00:06:37,510
For the time being,
I'll walk Mizuno home until this is settled.

66
00:06:38,560 --> 00:06:40,890
You wouldn't mind?

67
00:06:40,890 --> 00:06:43,430
Better to be cautious now,
then when it's too late.

68
00:06:45,790 --> 00:06:47,970
Thank you.

69
00:06:49,140 --> 00:06:52,170
That would put you at ease too, right, Sui?

70
00:06:52,170 --> 00:06:54,120
What?

71
00:06:54,120 --> 00:06:57,430
Oh, yes. Thank you.

72
00:06:58,120 --> 00:07:00,140
Please take care of her.

73
00:07:05,170 --> 00:07:10,620
Monou. I'll be heading out a bit,
then straight home.

74
00:07:10,620 --> 00:07:13,300
All right.

75
00:07:13,940 --> 00:07:15,380
Please take care.

76
00:07:15,380 --> 00:07:16,870
Thank you.

77
00:07:21,330 --> 00:07:23,340
- Ready?
- Yeah.

78
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:31,590
We'll be heading to do a deal with...

79
00:07:44,560 --> 00:07:48,000
Wait! I haven't said my piece yet!

80
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:50,850
Leave me alone. This plan is over!

81
00:07:50,850 --> 00:07:52,620
I want nothing to do with you anymore,

82
00:07:52,620 --> 00:07:55,240
so please, don't bother me again!

83
00:07:55,240 --> 00:07:58,010
Don't end things on your own terms!

84
00:07:58,010 --> 00:08:01,540
I said I'd figure this out!

85
00:08:01,540 --> 00:08:03,260
Damn you...

86
00:08:05,160 --> 00:08:06,830
Sui?

87
00:08:10,680 --> 00:08:13,690
Sui! Sui, Sui, Sui!

88
00:08:13,690 --> 00:08:17,030
I knew you'd come back for me.

89
00:08:17,030 --> 00:08:18,820
- What? No!
- Sui.

90
00:08:18,820 --> 00:08:23,020
I'll always love you. I still do.

91
00:08:23,020 --> 00:08:25,740
So, rest easy, okay?

92
00:08:25,740 --> 00:08:28,430
You've clearly misunderstood.

93
00:08:29,070 --> 00:08:31,670
I have no lingering attachments to you.

94
00:08:31,670 --> 00:08:36,010
I don't plan on ever seeing you again.

95
00:08:36,800 --> 00:08:39,180
No, but...

96
00:08:39,900 --> 00:08:42,300
I'm here...

97
00:08:42,300 --> 00:08:45,430
because I have business with Takizawa.

98
00:08:47,690 --> 00:08:50,890
Really now.

99
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:55,520
Come to laugh at my pathetic fate?

100
00:08:55,520 --> 00:09:00,160
Or have you changed your mind about my plan?

101
00:09:00,160 --> 00:09:01,600
Neither.

102
00:09:01,600 --> 00:09:04,040
Then what exactly do you want?

103
00:09:05,500 --> 00:09:08,600
You're free to harass me as you wish.

104
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:15,080
But don't drag irrelevant parties
like Mizuno into our troubles.

105
00:09:15,080 --> 00:09:17,620
Please.

106
00:09:17,620 --> 00:09:19,410
What are you talking about?

107
00:09:19,410 --> 00:09:21,560
Who the heck is Mizuno?

108
00:09:21,560 --> 00:09:24,230
- You saw her when you visited.
- What?

109
00:09:24,230 --> 00:09:26,810
- You went all the way to Sui's office?
- Oh!

110
00:09:26,810 --> 00:09:30,950
That dreary woman who chased me out the door?

111
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:34,820
I don't have time to bother people like her.

112
00:09:34,820 --> 00:09:37,200
The only one I have a grudge on

113
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:41,110
is the person who ruined my plan - you.

114
00:09:46,880 --> 00:09:50,800
Oh, I know that irritating look.

115
00:09:50,800 --> 00:09:56,310
Always standing up for others,
but never yourself.

116
00:09:56,310 --> 00:09:58,710
Why would you even do such a thing?

117
00:10:00,260 --> 00:10:02,660
First of all.

118
00:10:05,100 --> 00:10:07,510
The only reason why this man chose you

119
00:10:07,510 --> 00:10:11,500
was because he pitied you
after you lost your parents.

120
00:10:11,500 --> 00:10:13,030
Huh?

121
00:10:15,180 --> 00:10:17,630
You think you're so special.

122
00:10:17,630 --> 00:10:21,390
Even I clawed my way
through my own struggles.

123
00:10:21,390 --> 00:10:25,320
And just when I thought
I'd finally reached the top...

124
00:10:27,130 --> 00:10:30,020
You had to use your cowardly pity tactics.

125
00:10:30,020 --> 00:10:33,110
How dare you get a head start on me?

126
00:10:33,960 --> 00:10:36,250
What are you talking about?

127
00:10:38,570 --> 00:10:41,720
You should be thankful I'm so kind.

128
00:10:42,480 --> 00:10:46,570
I couldn't stand to see you rejected
because of your infertility.

129
00:10:46,570 --> 00:10:51,100
That's why I extended a helping hand!

130
00:10:51,100 --> 00:10:54,280
I had the perfect plan

131
00:10:54,280 --> 00:10:58,650
to make us all happy.

132
00:10:58,650 --> 00:11:00,670
But you.

133
00:11:00,670 --> 00:11:03,930
Both of you.

134
00:11:03,930 --> 00:11:07,480
Why turn down such a genius idea?

135
00:11:07,480 --> 00:11:12,100
Why not choose the path
that makes us all happy?

136
00:11:16,470 --> 00:11:19,770
I won't let my plan be ruined so easily.

137
00:11:29,100 --> 00:11:30,720
Sui?

138
00:11:32,930 --> 00:11:34,820
Good bye.

139
00:11:47,100 --> 00:11:48,730
Hey, a striped mullet.

140
00:12:16,050 --> 00:12:20,270
<i>I have to do what I ought to do.</i>

141
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:35,600
[MIREVO DESIGN]

142
00:12:54,020 --> 00:12:58,330
[Interior Design Coordinator]

143
00:12:58,330 --> 00:13:02,730
[Hirose Architects]

144
00:13:14,450 --> 00:13:16,530
Excuse me.

145
00:13:16,530 --> 00:13:18,500
We're going to be using this room soon.

146
00:13:18,500 --> 00:13:21,960
Sorry. Lunch break must already be over.

147
00:13:23,540 --> 00:13:25,670
I admire your intense concentration.

148
00:13:25,670 --> 00:13:28,010
You seem really motivated to study.

149
00:13:28,010 --> 00:13:29,350
You think so?

150
00:13:29,350 --> 00:13:32,480
It's like you're absorbed in your work.

151
00:13:34,860 --> 00:13:38,600
All I can do now is my best.

152
00:13:38,600 --> 00:13:41,090
There's plenty I'm still not used to,

153
00:13:41,090 --> 00:13:44,200
so I'm causing trouble to the team.

154
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:46,270
Don't worry about that.

155
00:13:46,270 --> 00:13:47,800
What?

156
00:13:47,800 --> 00:13:50,590
We're all here for you, all right?

157
00:13:53,090 --> 00:13:55,330
Thank you.

158
00:13:59,910 --> 00:14:01,940
Would you like some coffee?

159
00:14:01,940 --> 00:14:03,340
I'll get some myself, thanks.

160
00:14:03,340 --> 00:14:05,500
[Idea Construction Office]

161
00:14:07,660 --> 00:14:10,090
A proposal for an event?

162
00:14:10,090 --> 00:14:11,930
Yeah.

163
00:14:11,930 --> 00:14:13,880
Since it's being held by a partner of ours,

164
00:14:13,880 --> 00:14:16,430
we were asked to lend a hand.

165
00:14:16,430 --> 00:14:18,270
I see.

166
00:14:18,270 --> 00:14:22,470
Do you know Takaomi Hirose,
of Hirose Architects?

167
00:14:22,470 --> 00:14:24,860
Yes, of course.

168
00:14:24,860 --> 00:14:28,640
I've known the kid since he was a student.

169
00:14:28,640 --> 00:14:30,910
- Really?
- Yeah.

170
00:14:30,910 --> 00:14:36,220
We've always wanted to work together,
but never found the opportunity.

171
00:14:36,220 --> 00:14:42,450
So, I'm hoping to rope him in
to help us with this event.

172
00:14:43,080 --> 00:14:46,080
Monou, want to be our representative?

173
00:14:48,750 --> 00:14:52,610
I'd be honored to have the opportunity.

174
00:14:52,610 --> 00:14:55,060
All right, I'll put in a word for you.

175
00:14:55,060 --> 00:14:58,680
Draft a proposal
and go visit him in the coming days.

176
00:14:58,680 --> 00:15:01,140
I'll have Mao support you.

177
00:15:01,140 --> 00:15:03,100
- What?
- He's Hirose's junior.

178
00:15:03,100 --> 00:15:06,760
They attended the same seminar.

179
00:15:06,760 --> 00:15:08,620
That's amazing.

180
00:15:09,610 --> 00:15:12,870
I'll try not to disappoint, Mr. Hoshina.

181
00:15:15,520 --> 00:15:18,680
Sorry to drag you out. I know you're busy.

182
00:15:18,680 --> 00:15:20,720
It's fine.

183
00:15:20,720 --> 00:15:22,860
Can't defy the boss's orders, you know?

184
00:15:23,870 --> 00:15:28,370
I didn't realize you attended
a seminar with Hirose.

185
00:15:28,370 --> 00:15:30,500
That's really amazing.

186
00:15:30,500 --> 00:15:35,430
We never attended at the same time, though.

187
00:15:35,430 --> 00:15:39,540
I know him, but he certainly doesn't know me.

188
00:15:39,540 --> 00:15:45,240
Still, I feel better having you come with me.

189
00:15:46,630 --> 00:15:49,760
Glad I could help.

190
00:15:49,760 --> 00:15:52,810
This is my first time
presenting an idea of mine.

191
00:15:52,810 --> 00:15:55,470
I'm getting a bit nervous...

192
00:15:55,470 --> 00:15:57,510
You'll be fine.

193
00:15:58,540 --> 00:16:00,910
Remember, you're not alone.

194
00:16:02,570 --> 00:16:04,350
Thanks.

195
00:16:06,250 --> 00:16:07,930
- Ready?
- Yeah.

196
00:16:10,300 --> 00:16:14,730
[Hirose Architects]

197
00:16:17,960 --> 00:16:19,800
Did I keep you waiting?

198
00:16:19,800 --> 00:16:23,970
Not at all. Thank you for seeing us today.

199
00:16:26,520 --> 00:16:29,620
My name is Monou
of Idea Construction Office.

200
00:16:29,620 --> 00:16:34,030
I'm Hirose. Let Mr. Hoshina know
I send my regards.

201
00:16:34,030 --> 00:16:37,340
- My business card.
- Thank you, and mine.

202
00:16:37,340 --> 00:16:38,790
My name is Tsukidome.

203
00:16:38,790 --> 00:16:41,840
We actually graduated from the same seminar.

204
00:16:41,840 --> 00:16:44,080
Really?

205
00:16:44,080 --> 00:16:46,050
What a fun coincidence.

206
00:16:46,050 --> 00:16:48,430
- For you.
- Thank you. And mine as well.

207
00:16:50,530 --> 00:16:52,330
To start,

208
00:16:52,330 --> 00:16:56,870
I've summarized our vision for this event.

209
00:16:56,870 --> 00:16:58,670
Please, take a look.

210
00:16:58,670 --> 00:17:00,250
Thank you.

211
00:17:09,720 --> 00:17:11,360
[Contents]

212
00:17:11,360 --> 00:17:12,680
[Event Specifications]

213
00:17:20,410 --> 00:17:24,050
Mr. Hirose.

214
00:17:24,050 --> 00:17:28,300
I know you must receive
plenty of offers like this.

215
00:17:28,300 --> 00:17:30,900
That I do, yes.

216
00:17:30,900 --> 00:17:36,920
However, I must let you know
your designs are special to me.

217
00:17:38,580 --> 00:17:42,890
Before I moved, there was a cafe
I was quite fond of in the neighborhood.

218
00:17:42,890 --> 00:17:46,210
I never felt uncomfortable there.

219
00:17:46,210 --> 00:17:49,880
Being there motivated me to face the day.

220
00:17:49,880 --> 00:17:54,490
It was sort of like a power spot of mine.

221
00:17:54,490 --> 00:17:56,500
I see.

222
00:17:56,500 --> 00:18:02,270
I discovered the place was your design
after entering this line of work.

223
00:18:03,350 --> 00:18:05,780
Is that so?

224
00:18:05,780 --> 00:18:08,290
I'm sure the cafe felt so comforting

225
00:18:08,290 --> 00:18:13,600
because of your kindness
and careful planning.

226
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:15,240
That is why...

227
00:18:21,290 --> 00:18:22,690
Monou.

228
00:18:22,690 --> 00:18:23,960
Yes?

229
00:18:23,960 --> 00:18:28,690
I do receive quite a few offers like yours.

230
00:18:28,690 --> 00:18:33,740
But most clients could care less
whether it was my work or not.

231
00:18:33,740 --> 00:18:35,250
I see.

232
00:18:35,830 --> 00:18:40,520
However, seeing how passionate
you are about my work,

233
00:18:40,520 --> 00:18:43,990
I think we can create a wonderful event.

234
00:18:43,990 --> 00:18:45,470
What?

235
00:18:51,750 --> 00:18:57,490
Next time, I would love to see an idea
that is wholly your own.

236
00:18:58,360 --> 00:19:01,680
Yes, I'll be sure to bring one.

237
00:19:05,340 --> 00:19:08,830
Since we've ended early,
how about we grab a meal together?

238
00:19:08,830 --> 00:19:10,790
You wouldn't mind?

239
00:19:11,450 --> 00:19:14,050
I'm sorry, but I have prior plans.

240
00:19:14,050 --> 00:19:15,780
That's too bad.

241
00:19:15,780 --> 00:19:19,660
Then how about the two of us, Monou?

242
00:19:19,660 --> 00:19:22,410
I'd love to join you.

243
00:19:23,050 --> 00:19:25,440
There's a place we've designed right nearby.

244
00:19:25,440 --> 00:19:26,990
How about we go there?

245
00:19:26,990 --> 00:19:30,710
That sounds wonderful.
I can't wait to see it.

246
00:19:30,710 --> 00:19:33,300
Actually, this is that very store.

247
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:36,080
I've been here before.

248
00:19:36,080 --> 00:19:37,340
- Really?
- Yes.

249
00:19:37,340 --> 00:19:39,450
The terrace was especially beautiful.

250
00:19:39,450 --> 00:19:41,330
I'm honored, thank you.

251
00:19:51,520 --> 00:19:54,070
You're drinking fast tonight.

252
00:19:54,070 --> 00:19:57,130
- Am not.
- And you're in a bad mood.

253
00:19:57,130 --> 00:19:58,770
Am not.

254
00:19:58,770 --> 00:20:01,040
Did you fight with a girlfriend?

255
00:20:01,040 --> 00:20:03,240
I don't have a girlfriend.

256
00:20:03,240 --> 00:20:05,950
Then you have someone
you're guarding, but not dating.

257
00:20:05,950 --> 00:20:09,650
Again? You haven't changed since college.

258
00:20:09,650 --> 00:20:11,670
I'm telling you, that's not it.

259
00:20:11,670 --> 00:20:16,050
Mao just can't ignore people in need.

260
00:20:16,050 --> 00:20:20,200
When will you learn the difference
between romance and compassion?

261
00:20:20,200 --> 00:20:22,550
Helping someone does not equal dating them.

262
00:20:22,550 --> 00:20:24,400
I know that already.

263
00:20:24,400 --> 00:20:27,570
You definitely don't.

264
00:20:27,570 --> 00:20:29,450
Yeah, whatever.

265
00:20:30,470 --> 00:20:34,760
By the way, do you all know Hirose?
The one who also attended our seminar.

266
00:20:34,760 --> 00:20:37,200
Takaomi Hirose?

267
00:20:37,200 --> 00:20:39,250
The legendary architect?

268
00:20:39,250 --> 00:20:41,690
- Winner of the Goro Nomura award?
- Yeah.

269
00:20:41,690 --> 00:20:44,210
I've got a job with him coming up.

270
00:20:44,210 --> 00:20:45,880
- Really?
- That's amazing.

271
00:20:45,880 --> 00:20:47,130
He must be a real ladies man.

272
00:20:47,130 --> 00:20:50,800
That's what you're focused on?

273
00:20:50,800 --> 00:20:53,740
But he's married, right?

274
00:20:53,740 --> 00:20:55,320
Is he?

275
00:20:55,320 --> 00:20:57,060
See, look.

276
00:20:57,060 --> 00:20:58,860
His wife's a beauty.

277
00:20:58,860 --> 00:21:02,530
- Woah, she is.
- Married, huh?

278
00:21:05,610 --> 00:21:07,190
You look happy.

279
00:21:07,190 --> 00:21:10,080
What? I don't.

280
00:21:10,080 --> 00:21:12,620
Now he's back to sulking.

281
00:21:12,620 --> 00:21:14,250
Yikes.

282
00:21:14,250 --> 00:21:16,550
What a complicated fella.

283
00:21:22,550 --> 00:21:24,640
Why're not opening?

284
00:21:29,810 --> 00:21:31,770
Mao?

285
00:21:34,050 --> 00:21:36,860
What're you doing?

286
00:21:36,860 --> 00:21:39,270
I was taking out the trash.

287
00:21:41,640 --> 00:21:45,870
You were drinking, at this hour?

288
00:21:45,870 --> 00:21:49,340
Are you drunk?

289
00:21:52,100 --> 00:21:53,820
Let me see that.

290
00:22:02,030 --> 00:22:04,010
Are you okay?

291
00:22:05,450 --> 00:22:07,270
Water.

292
00:22:07,270 --> 00:22:10,020
Oh, jeez...

293
00:22:10,020 --> 00:22:11,730
Can you walk?

294
00:22:17,010 --> 00:22:20,050
Here. Drink up.

295
00:22:30,350 --> 00:22:32,970
Thanks for today.

296
00:22:32,970 --> 00:22:36,430
I appreciated you being there with me.

297
00:22:38,890 --> 00:22:41,770
The meal with Hirose was quite fun.

298
00:22:41,770 --> 00:22:44,020
He gave me plenty of hints
for my next proposal.

299
00:22:44,020 --> 00:22:46,190
You should join us next time...

300
00:22:54,150 --> 00:22:56,050
Mao?

301
00:22:58,540 --> 00:23:01,280
Do you feel ill?

302
00:23:06,800 --> 00:23:11,680
It's like when we first met.
Except, now we're reversed.

303
00:23:25,240 --> 00:23:27,070
Sui.

304
00:23:28,610 --> 00:23:32,430
Want to pick up where we left off that night?

305
00:23:45,460 --> 00:23:48,050
What do you think of Mao?

306
00:23:48,050 --> 00:23:50,320
You seem angry.

307
00:23:50,320 --> 00:23:53,210
I'd rather focus on making do on my own.

308
00:23:53,210 --> 00:23:55,710
I'm worried about you too, Sui.

309
00:23:55,710 --> 00:23:57,840
Mao, I love you.

310
00:23:57,840 --> 00:24:00,000
I've always loved you.

